    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Staffs culminating in an ornament such as a pine cone and sometimes decorated with ivy or wine leaves. In Greek mythology, the staff belonged to Dionysos and his followers. These were used as sacred instruments during religious rituals and celebrations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
